ACDS Navigation

The main navigation component is intended to be used as the primary means of navigation around the website. It typically accommodates the top level of the information architecture. Organize pages in a tree to indicate hierarchy. The menu item also support display badge.

COMPONENT NAME 

  

acdsNavigation 

  


ANATOMY 

 

The navigation component is comprised of a large container that holds all of the navigation menu sub-items. These sub items are shown as text; when a user interacts with these text items, the colorful overlay component appears and so does the active text. This gives the user visual feedback to know the current system status.  



1.   Container: Holds all of the components and elements that make up a navigation component. 

2.   Active Text: Shows what element the user has clicked on and is actively engaged with. 

3.   Text : This text represents different menu options that the user can click on to navigate to a different part of the website 

4.   Colourful Overlay & Icon: Acts as a divider between the upper menu items and the lower ‘My Account’ menu items. 

 

(Note: the default Log out menu item in the My Account menu does not contain any code implementation) 



USAGE


There are two ways to use the Navigation component: 

  • In Experience cloud, from the Component List, drag and drop the Navigation component onto a page layout slot. To make the component appear in every page, drop the component onto a shared layout slot. Customize the component in the Properties popup. 
  • Include the navigation component in a custom LWC to feed dynamic data into the Navigation component. 


The Navigation component is design to work closely with the Header and Footer components to create optimal responsive user experience, they work best when using the ACDS theme layout to arrange the three components together in Experience cloud environment. See more detail on ACDS theme layout page.

componentAttributes.richTextValue: Site navigation menu and My Account menu

COMPONENT ATTRIBUTES


Name Type Description
homeLabel String Label for home header
homepageUrl String Url for the home header
mainMenuList Json object Json object for the Site Navigation menu
includeAccount Boolean Show My Account menu
accountMenuLabel String Label for the my account header
accountMenuList Json object Json object for the My Account menu


SITE NAVIGATION MENU JSON ITEM ATTRIBUTES


Name Type Description
label String Item label
name String Item unique ID
expanded Boolean Expanded the item if it’s a folder: true or false
href String Item url
badgeType String Badge type: new, new-inverse, error, error-inverse, warning, warning-inverse, info, info-inverse
badgeCount String Badge value (number)
items Json list Sub menu items


MY ACCOUNT MENU JSON ITEM ATTRIBUTES


Name Type Description
label String Item label
name String Item unique ID
href String Item url


SLOTS


Name Description
default Placeholder for content below the My Account menu.


METHODS


Name Description
menuselect Simulates a mouse click on the Site Navigation menu item
accountselect Simulates a mouse click on the My Account menu item

Use Navigation component inside a LWC to allow the following function: 

  • Add event listener for the Site Navigation menu event 
  • Add event listener for the My Account menu event 
  • Add custom content default slots below the My Account menu 
  • Allow dynamic data feed into the component 

  

    

Template: 


<c-acds-navigation 

       include-account="true" 

       items={items} 

        onmenuselect={handleNavTreeSelect} 

        onaccountselect={handleAccountSelect} 

       > 

       <br/> 

       <div class="slds-align_absolute-center"> 

           <p>This is external content</p><br> 

           <img src="/assets/localdev/images/logo.svg"/> 

       </div> 

       <br/> 

   </c-acds-navigation> 

  

Javascript: 

  

    handleNavTreeSelect(event) { 

       console.log(event.detail.name); 

   } 

  

    handleAccountSelect(event) { 

       console.log(event.detail.name); 

   }
